# iKali tool registry — single source of truth.
# Format (pipe-separated):  name|category|method|package_or_binary|ish_ok|description
#   name        display name
#   category    network|web|password|osint|traffic|exploit|wireless|reverse|forensics|ssl|mobile|c2|reporting|utils|base
#   method      apk|pip|go|gem|git|source|special
#   package     install token / resolved binary used for status checks
#   ish_ok      yes|no|partial   (works under iSH?)
#   description short one-liner
#
# Lines beginning with # and blank lines are ignored.

# --- base ---
curl|base|apk|curl|yes|Transfer data from URLs
wget|base|apk|wget|yes|Network downloader
git|base|apk|git|yes|Version control / clone tools
python3|base|apk|python3|yes|Python 3 interpreter
py3-pip|base|apk|pip3|yes|Python package installer
ruby|base|apk|ruby|yes|Ruby interpreter
go|base|apk|go|partial|Go toolchain (slow under emulation)
perl|base|apk|perl|yes|Perl interpreter
tmux|base|apk|tmux|yes|Terminal multiplexer
vim|base|apk|vim|yes|Text editor
jq|base|apk|jq|yes|JSON processor
tar|base|apk|tar|yes|Archive utility
unzip|base|apk|unzip|yes|Zip extractor
build-base|base|apk|gcc|partial|Compiler toolchain for source builds

